<stack-static>
<statement><div><p>Find the magnitude of each of the following vectors. Give your answers as integers or exact surds (e.g. <c>sqrt(13)</c>).</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>
        <p>
            <m> \mathbf{a} = {\left[\begin{array}{c} 4 \\ -3 \end{array}\right]} </m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Magnitude <m> |\mathbf{a}| = </m> <fillin characters="6" name="ans1"/>  
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>
            <m> \mathbf{b} = {\left[\begin{array}{c} -8 \\ 0 \end{array}\right]} </m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Magnitude <m> |\mathbf{b}| = </m> <fillin characters="6" name="ans2"/>  
        </p>
    </li>
</ol></div></statement>
<solution><div><h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p>The magnitude (or length) of a column vector <m>\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \end{pmatrix}</m> is given by the formula:</p>
<me> |\mathbf{v}| = \sqrt{x^2 + y^2} </me>

<p><alert>Part (a)</alert></p>
<p>For <m>\mathbf{a} = {\left[\begin{array}{c} 4 \\ -3 \end{array}\right]}</m>:</p>
<me> |\mathbf{a}| = \sqrt{({4})^2 + ({-3})^2} </me>
<me> |\mathbf{a}| = \sqrt{{16} + {9}} </me>
<me> |\mathbf{a}| = \sqrt{{25}} = {5} </me>

<p><alert>Part (b)</alert></p>
<p>For <m>\mathbf{b} = {\left[\begin{array}{c} -8 \\ 0 \end{array}\right]}</m>:</p>
<me> |\mathbf{b}| = \sqrt{({-8})^2 + ({0})^2} </me>
<me> |\mathbf{b}| = \sqrt{{64} + {0}} </me>
<me> |\mathbf{b}| = \sqrt{{64}} </me>
<p>
    If the number under the square root is not a perfect square, we leave it in exact surd form:
    <m> \mathbf{8} </m>
</p></div></solution>
<answer><p><m>5</m></p></answer>
<answer><p><m>8</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>